caption: This is my 1st time ordering from this location and the Pizza and Service is Great

After reading so many poor reviews I still decided to give this place a try, through friends and con worked I've heard of this place and I've heard it is A-MAZING! Now I do not understand why people only want to review a place when there's something wrong with their order or a mishap, but let me tell you all, the food was unbelievably well made and the presentation was great. I ordered a 16' Classic combo for dinner for my husband and I, and though when I called in the girl who took my order, Vanessa, sounded like she was in a very busy environment, she still took the time with all the patience to answer each and every one of my questions throughly, like wow! So much attention to the customers. The presentation again was great, loved the way the pizza look and obviously the taste didn't fall behind, it was just as we had heard and expected. Did not disappoint! As far as delivery, again, we did hear it busy in the background and the young lady did mention they were definitely busy and that it would take an additional 15-20 minutes for my delivery, no prob!!!! When my driver arrived, he was following all protocols as far as COVID, and the food was hot and in good condition. 10/10! Would recommend ♥️♥️ Do not listen to the bad reviews, restaurants only get reviews when something bad happens or a misunderstanding, never when they do a great job! This place is great!

I’ll never order from here again! Ordered through GH and the order was dropped off at some other apt by their own driver who called and said “food delivered” and hung up. Even though my apt or unit was not right. The person at the restaurant said they had the right apt - that driver had a picture and then said as a “courtesy” we can remake it and deliver again. The order finally arrived 2 hours later - no one called or said anything and left it in the lobby - we casually found it sitting there while coming back from walking our dog. The order was still wrong and only ONE item was sent -(chicken parm sandwich) it was cold - it was undercooked - it was all shaken up and it was a completely mediocre presentation and the taste was terrible. Oh - the receipt had some other address or unit - not even mine or what is under my Grubhub info! Extremely poor customer service and literally no attention to what they’re doing! Save yourself a night of no dinner! Don’t order from this place!

I found out the food had been sitting unattended in a public place for about 45min (which, to be fair, means the delivery was pretty quick).  It was cold and I had no intention of eating it any more.  I asked what they could to do to fix it, I was still hungry, thinking they might redeliver hot food to the right address.  Instead they offered to refund my order which was fine but not what I expected.  The kicker is they never actually refunded the order!  It was an honest mistake and an easy enough fix. They just didn't seem to have any interest in fixing it.

Let me start out by saying Rosati's makes a great pizza. Unfortunately, I don't care for the shady appearance of their pricing. We ordered a 20 inch pizza, don't even see that size on the menu but okay, and the cost came to about $28. We ordered 1/2 black Olives and the other Jalapeno Peppers and they charged us the full $3 for each ingredient bringing our pie to about $40. The problem is we have purchased in the past and each time there seems to be differing costs and no matter the pie an increase in price with no rhyme or reason for the pricing. Yes, we have gotten different types in the past but, Why we paid $40 for a thin pizza with 2 half toppings made absolutely no sense  and things are beginning to look shady on our bills so as much as I enjoy their pizza I and my family will have to look elsewhere for a pizza in Chicago, there are many.

I placed an order for delivery.  I waited 30min past the latest delivery time to call Rosatis to see why it was so late. The female who answered the phone was rude, unapologetic and could not give me a delivery time. She claimed they were very busy. That’s your excuse for rudeness and failure to deliver in a reasonable time?  Not to mention not having the ability to provide me a time at all?  You claim you are a manager, shouldn’t you know the time your kitchen is running on based on orders received, employees and preparation time?  Seems to me with all the restaurants struggling and all of the people in the industry out of work,  that you would try to retain your customers and not complain about being busy and using that as your extremely poor excuse for bad service. As far as the attitude and general lack of any kind of care or respect for me as a customer, this woman should not be a manager. As an employee of a restaurant right now, you should be thankful and grateful you have customers at all. I trusted you to make my food and not pass on a virus to me. You took that trust and threw it in the trash. You have lost a long time customer.
